  "prompt": "Why isn't my toilet tank filling up with water?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why your toilet tank isn't filling up with water:\n\n1. Water supply valve\n- Valve might be partially or fully closed\n- Check the valve near the base of the toilet and ensure it's fully open\n\n2. Faulty fill valve\n- The fill valve may be damaged or worn out\n- Could require adjustment or replacement\n\n3. Broken float\n- The float mechanism might be stuck or not functioning correctly\n- This prevents the tank from filling properly\n\n4. Clogged water supply line\n- Mineral buildup or debris could be blocking water flow\n- May need cleaning or replacement\n\n5. Low water pressure\n- Issues with home's main water supply\n- Check if other fixtures are experiencing similar problems\n\n6. Kinked water supply line\n- The flexible line connecting the valve to the toilet might be twisted\n- Straighten or replace the line\n\n7. Cracked tank\n- Rare, but possible\n- Inspect for visible cracks or leaks\n\nTo diagnose the issue, try checking these potential causes step by step. If you're unsure or uncomfortable troubleshooting, consider calling a plumber.",
